The paper deals with the classification of hyperspectral images using a machine learning approach, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves probabilistic modeling and optimization, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of extreme learning machine (ELM) and weighted composite features (WCFs) suggests a neural network approach (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT).
